Module kivakit.core
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count

Class Range<Value extends IntegerNumeric<Value>>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.Range<Value>
Type Parameters:
Value - A value that is IntegerNumeric, which includes Minimizable, Maximizable, Comparable, and NextValue.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Countable, Sized, DoubleQuantizable, Quantizable, QuantumComparable<Countable>, Stringable, StringSource, Comparable<Countable>
public class Range<Value extends IntegerNumeric<Value>> extends Object implements Comparable<Countable>, QuantumComparable<Countable>, Countable
Represents a range of value objects from a minimum to a maximum.

Creation and Properties

Ranges can be created in two ways, as rangeExclusive(IntegerNumeric, IntegerNumeric) ranges which do not include their maximum value, and as rangeInclusive(IntegerNumeric, IntegerNumeric) ranges which do.

  • rangeInclusive(IntegerNumeric, IntegerNumeric)
  • rangeExclusive(IntegerNumeric, IntegerNumeric)
  • upperBound()
  • isInclusive()
  • isExclusive()
  • minimum()
  • inclusiveMaximum()
  • exclusiveMaximum()

Looping

The values in a range can be processed in a loop with these methods.

  • forEach(LoopBody)
  • forCount(Count, FilteredLoopBody)
  • loop(Runnable)

Operations

  • constrain(Value)
  • contains(Value)
  • randomValue(Random)
